item.title: Ello add a quote by Ayn Rand
item.description: "When I die I hope to go to heaven--whatever that is--and I want to be able to afford the price of admission." -- Ayn Rand

item.title: Ello add a quote by William Shakespeare
item.description: "I have of late--but wherefore I know not--lost all my mirth, forgone all custom of exercises; and indeed it goes so heavily with my disposition that this goodly frame, the earth, seems to me a sterile promontory, this most excellent canopy, the air, look you, this brave o'erhanging firmament, this majestical roof fretted with golden fire, why, it appears no other thing to me than a foul and pestilent congregation of vapours." -- William Shakespeare
